Quick fix to the issue I opened here: https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/487  Added the overloaded method fit(INDArray data  int nDims) to BarnesHutTsne; changed the method plot so that it calls this new fit method instead of calling fit(INDArray data) -> the parameterr nDims of the plot method is no longer unused.

Fix for the issue I've opened [here](https://github.com/deeplearning4j/deeplearning4j/issues/487)  Added the overloaded method fit(INDArray data  int nDims) to BarnesHutTsne; changed the method BarnesHutTsne.plot so that it now calls this new fit method instead of fit(INDArray data) -> the parameter nDims of the method plot is no longer unused  non-2D tSNE is now possible.

Nd4jTestSuite unit test errors from missing constructors  org.nd4j.linalg.Nd4jTestSuite.suite attempts to find the constructors of all subclasses of BaseNd4jTest that take String name and a Nd4jBackend backend parameters. Not all these classes had constructors that matched this prototype.  The fix is to add constructors that call the superclass.
